- This is conversion copy — every sentence moves the buyer toward a purchase decision
- Lead with buyer benefit, not specs — specs support the benefit, they never lead
- Use buyer phrases from Section 5 naturally — speak their language
- Address each of the 5 buying objections directly in the relevant H2 section
- Honest cons build trust — the comparison table shows them; don't hide them in body copy
- Discount codes mentioned naturally near CTAs — not as a standalone paragraph
- Primary keyword `gel nail polish set` in `<strong>` tags every single mention — no exceptions
- No editorial literary hooks — open sections with buyer benefit or the buying question
- H2 sections are short and direct — buyers scan, they do not read long intros
- Conclusion = final push to purchase, not a summary
- Internal cluster links placed in H2 sections mid-post — after the first product CTA renders — anchor text natural, never forced
- No related articles section — site handles via component
- Language: American English — not British English
- No banned AI patterns: no "elevate," "seamlessly," "game-changing," "dive into," "transformative"
- No long em dashes — use comma or restructure
- Sentence rhythm varies — short punchy sentences for key selling points, longer for context
- No "we tested" language — write informed editorial observations from specs and verified buyer reviews

